## Join Types

| Join Type | Description | Use Case |
|-----------|-------------|----------|
| Inner | Matching rows only | Intersection |
| Left | All left rows + matching right | Primary table preservation |
| Right | All right rows + matching left | Secondary table preservation |
| Outer | All rows from both | Full outer join |
| Left Semi | Left rows with match in right | Existence check |
| Left Anti | Left rows without match in right | Exclusion check |

## Window Functions

### Ranking Functions
- **row_number()**: Unique sequential numbers
- **rank()**: Rank with gaps for ties
- **dense_rank()**: Rank without gaps

### Analytic Functions
- **lag()**: Previous row value
- **lead()**: Next row value
- **aggregate**: sum, avg, count over windows

## Complex Types

### Array Operations
- **explode()**: Flatten arrays to rows
- **array_contains()**: Check array membership
- **collect_list()**: Aggregate to array

### Map Operations
- **map_keys()**: Extract map keys
- **map_values()**: Extract map values
- **map_from_arrays()**: Create maps

### Struct Operations
- **col.***: Access struct fields
- **struct()**: Create structs from columns
